{"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/com.perimeterx.mobile-sdk\/documentation\/PerimeterX_SDK"]]},"identifier":{"interfaceLanguage":"swift","url":"doc:\/\/com.perimeterx.mobile-sdk\/documentation\/PerimeterX_SDK\/Migration"},"sections":[],"schemaVersion":{"patch":0,"major":0,"minor":3},"metadata":{"title":"Migration from earlier SDK versions","roleHeading":"Article","modules":[{"name":"PerimeterX_SDK"}],"role":"article"},"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"In this article we will explore how to upgrade the Perimeter X iOS SDK from an earlier version (1.x and below) to version 2.0."}],"variants":[{"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}],"paths":["\/documentation\/perimeterx_sdk\/migration"]},{"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"occ"}],"paths":["\/documentation\/perimeterx_sdk\/migration"]}],"primaryContentSections":[{"content":[{"type":"heading","level":3,"anchor":"Overview","text":"Overview"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The PerimeterX iOS SDK v2.0 includes a complete new set of APIs. The current integration implemented in your code with an earlier SDK version will have to be replaced as following."}]},{"type":"heading","text":"Start the SDK","anchor":"Start-the-SDK","level":3},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"In version 1.x, the ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"start"},{"text":" function is called with 2 parameters: ","type":"text"},{"code":"AppId","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" and "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"enableDoctorCheck"},{"text":" (the later was added in 1.16.0).","type":"text"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"In version 2.0, the "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/com.perimeterx.mobile-sdk\/documentation\/PerimeterX_SDK\/PerimeterX\/start(appId:delegate:enableDoctorCheck:completion:)","isActive":true},{"text":" function has additional parameters:","type":"text"}]},{"items":[{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"delegate"},{"type":"text","text":" ("},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"PerimeterXDelegate"},{"type":"text","text":") to handle the SDK’s events."}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"code":"completion handler","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" to handle the result of the start process.","type":"text"}]}]}],"type":"orderedList"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Notice that the new Interceptor will be enabled in 2.0. This has effect on the integration with the SDK, which is described in this document."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"level":3,"text":"Set custom parameters","anchor":"Set-custom-parameters","type":"heading"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"In version 1.x, the set custom parameters function is called with the dictionary parameter only."}]},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"In version 2.0, the "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/com.perimeterx.mobile-sdk\/documentation\/PerimeterX_SDK\/PerimeterX\/setCustomParameters(parameters:forAppId:completion:)","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" function has another optional param: the AppID. This is required only when using multiple AppIDs."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"level":3,"text":"Get VID","type":"heading","anchor":"Get-VID"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"In version 1.x, the get VID function is called without any parameters.","type":"text"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"In version 2.0, the "},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/com.perimeterx.mobile-sdk\/documentation\/PerimeterX_SDK\/PerimeterX\/vid(forAppId:)"},{"type":"text","text":" function has another optional param: the AppID. This is required only when using multiple AppIDs."}]},{"anchor":"Get-HTTP-headers","text":"Get HTTP headers","type":"heading","level":3},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"In version 1.x, the get HTTP headers function is called without any parameters.","type":"text"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"In version 2.0, the ","type":"text"},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/com.perimeterx.mobile-sdk\/documentation\/PerimeterX_SDK\/PerimeterX\/headersForURLRequest(forAppId:)"},{"text":" function has another optional param: the AppID. This is required only when using multiple AppIDs. Please note that now this function should NOT be used when the interceptor is enabled.","type":"text"}]},{"text":"Check error and handle response","anchor":"Check-error-and-handle-response","type":"heading","level":3},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"In version 1.x, a function is called to get the PX’s error response from the request’s response which called another function to handle the PX’s error response.","type":"text"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"In version 2.0 the flow is much easier:"}]},{"type":"orderedList","items":[{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"If the interceptor is enabled, simply check whether the request was blocked with the "},{"isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/com.perimeterx.mobile-sdk\/documentation\/PerimeterX_SDK\/PerimeterX\/isRequestBlockedError(error:)","type":"reference"},{"type":"text","text":" function."}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"If the interceptor is disabled, use the PerimeterX SDK to handle the response with the "},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/com.perimeterx.mobile-sdk\/documentation\/PerimeterX_SDK\/PerimeterX\/handleResponse(forAppId:data:response:)"},{"text":" function. If it was a blocked response, the SDK will handle it and the function will return ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"true"},{"type":"text","text":"."}]}]}]},{"level":3,"anchor":"Other-functions","type":"heading","text":"Other functions"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"All other functions in 1.x were removed from the SDK’s API. You can learn more about the integration with those articles:"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"items":[{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/com.perimeterx.mobile-sdk\/documentation\/PerimeterX_SDK\/IntegrationGuide","isActive":true},{"text":".","type":"text"}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"identifier":"doc:\/\/com.perimeterx.mobile-sdk\/documentation\/PerimeterX_SDK\/BeyondTheBasic","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":"."}]}]}],"type":"orderedList"}],"kind":"content"}],"kind":"article","references":{"doc://com.perimeterx.mobile-sdk/documentation/PerimeterX_SDK/PerimeterXErrorCode/requestWasBlocked":{"identifier":"doc:\/\/com.perimeterx.mobile-sdk\/documentation\/PerimeterX_SDK\/PerimeterXErrorCode\/requestWasBlocked","fragments":[{"text":"case","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"requestWasBlocked","kind":"identifier"}],"abstract":[],"role":"symbol","type":"topic","url":"\/documentation\/perimeterx_sdk\/perimeterxerrorcode\/requestwasblocked","kind":"symbol","title":"PerimeterXErrorCode.requestWasBlocked"},"doc://com.perimeterx.mobile-sdk/documentation/PerimeterX_SDK/PerimeterX/isRequestBlockedError(error:)":{"url":"\/documentation\/perimeterx_sdk\/perimeterx\/isrequestblockederror(error:)","title":"isRequestBlockedError(error:)","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Returns true if the error is "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/com.perimeterx.mobile-sdk\/documentation\/PerimeterX_SDK\/PerimeterXErrorCode\/requestWasBlocked"},{"type":"text","text":" error."}],"kind":"symbol","navigatorTitle":[{"text":"isRequestBlockedErrorWithError:","kind":"identifier"}],"type":"topic","identifier":"doc:\/\/com.perimeterx.mobile-sdk\/documentation\/PerimeterX_SDK\/PerimeterX\/isRequestBlockedError(error:)","role":"symbol","fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"static"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"keyword","text":"func"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"isRe